# NestJS Guard Dependencies

`@UseGuards(SomeGuard)` on controllers — module must resolve guard + all constructor deps at startup.

- Declare shared guards in auth/security module; export guard + modules/providers its constructor needs.
- Guard gets new dep → update exporting module immediately.
- Add/update DI smoke test compiling at least one feature module with guard without manually providing new dep.
- `lint`, `build`, controller unit tests not enough — Nest DI errors often only at module compile/startup.

Example:

```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [UserClientModule, JwtModule.registerAsync(...)],
  providers: [JwtAuthGuard],
  exports: [UserClientModule, JwtModule, JwtAuthGuard],
})
export class AuthModule {}
```
